metadata.description:
I never went to college, and I never had a "crazy phase," so I didn't try Jägermeister until this past summer. I met a guy who said he used to drink at least one large bottle of it before he went to a party. Every time, without fail. He was a rugby player, so maybe that's normal? I thought that was the craziest thing I have ever heard. I did end up drinking a bottle with him.. and it wasn't horrible tasting. I can't lie. 

I couldn't sleep one night a few months ago, so I got up at around 3am and I wrote this song. It might be one of the strangest on the album, but that's why I like it. It's a story of the man I fell for this summer.

This is 5/8 of my album "when you feel like dying'. 

Written, produced, and mixed by me.
metadata.name: Jägermeister #1
metadata.title: Jägermeister
